# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# .env.production.example  — copy to .env.production
# Fill with real secrets — NEVER commit .env.production.
# (For local dev use qa-chatbot/.env.example instead.)
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── App ──────────────────────────────────────────
APP_NAME=qa-chatbot
APP_VERSION=0.1.0            # set to the build SHA in CI for deploy visibility
ENVIRONMENT=production
DEBUG=false
PRODUCTION_APPLICATION=true  # full-quality MAP-RPE tier
API_V1_PREFIX=/api/v1
# Real frontend origin(s) as a JSON list. NEVER use "*".
CORS_ORIGIN=["https://yourdomain.com"]

# ── Database (internal Docker hostname in prod) ──
DATABASE_URL=postgresql+asyncpg://postgres:STRONG_PASSWORD@postgres:5432/qa_chatbot
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=STRONG_PASSWORD_HERE
DATABASE_POOL_SIZE=20
DATABASE_MAX_OVERFLOW=40

# ── Redis (use a password in prod) ───────────────
REDIS_URL=redis://:REDIS_PASSWORD_HERE@redis:6379/0
REDIS_TTL_SECONDS=3600

# ── LLM (OpenRouter routes all model calls) ──────
OPENROUTER_API_KEY=sk-or-your-production-key
DEFAULT_MODEL=openai/gpt-4o-mini
COUNCIL_MODELS=["claude-sonnet-4-20250514","gpt-4o"]

# ── Supabase Auth (all four required) ────────────
SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-supabase-service-role-key
SUPABASE_JWT_SECRET=your-supabase-jwt-secret

# ── Rate limiting / request hardening ────────────
RATE_LIMIT_REQUESTS=100
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW_SECONDS=60
MAX_REQUEST_BODY_BYTES=1048576
REQUEST_TIMEOUT_SECONDS=60

# ── Error tracking (leave blank to disable) ──────
SENTRY_DSN=

# ── Object storage (MinIO / S3-compatible) ───────
MINIO_ENDPOINT_URL=http://minio:9000
MINIO_BUCKET_NAME=promptly
MINIO_ACCESS_KEY=CHANGE_ME
MINIO_SECRET_KEY=CHANGE_ME

# ── Process tuning (read by entrypoint/compose) ──
WORKERS=4
PORT=8000
LOG_LEVEL=info
CELERY_CONCURRENCY=8

# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Frontend image build args (NEXT_PUBLIC_* are inlined at BUILD time).
# docker-compose reads these via ${VAR} interpolation from the SHELL env or a
# `.env` file beside docker-compose.prod.yml — NOT from this env_file. Export them
# (or add to that .env) before `docker compose -f docker-compose.prod.yml build`.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_URL=https://yourdomain.com
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=https://your-project-ref.supabase.co
# NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-supabase-anon-key
